{
  "slug": "colour-and-weave-four-shaft-sample",
  "title": "Colour and weave on four shafts",
  "subtitle": "How alternating warp and weft colours create visual patterns in plain weave",
  "excerpt": "Colour-and-weave effects need no complex tie-up: the pattern emerges from the interaction of two alternating warp colours and two alternating weft colours in plain weave. Log cabin is the classic two-shaft version; M's and O's extends the principle across four shafts for richer block patterns.",
  "type": "TECHNIQUE",
