  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Colour-and-weave effects are sometimes called optical weaves. The pattern comes from the interaction of thread colours, not from a complex structure. In "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "plain weave",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "plain-weave"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " with two alternating "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "warp",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "warp"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " colours and two alternating "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "weft",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "weft"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " colours, the eye reads stripes, checks, or geometric blocks depending on how the colours pair up. The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "colour-and-weave",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "colour-and-weave"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " principle shows how much visual complexity is available from the simplest structure."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "suppliesCard",
        "attrs": {
          "items": [
            "Four-shaft floor loom (or rigid heddle loom for the log-cabin section)",
            "Two contrasting warp colours, same yarn weight (8/2 cotton works well)",
            "Two contrasting weft colours, ideally the same two yarns used in the warp",
            "Warping board",
            "Reed hook",
            "Two boat shuttles (one per weft colour)",
            "Scissors",
            "Tape measure",
            "Graph paper for planning the colour repeat"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Log cabin: the two-shaft foundation"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Before moving to four shafts it is worth understanding "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "log cabin",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "log-cabin"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " as the basic form. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Log cabin",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "log-cabin"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " uses two shafts and a strict alternating "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "colour repeat",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "colour-repeat"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ": colour A on shaft 1, colour B on shaft 2, throughout. In the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "weft",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "weft"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", colour A and colour B alternate on every pick."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "When the weft colour matches the warp colour it sits over, it blends in and disappears. When it contrasts, it shows."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Alternating A and B weft on every pick with A-B warp threading produces a checked pattern."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Weaving several picks of colour A before switching to colour B produces horizontal stripes."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Planning the warp colour repeat"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The visual effect depends entirely on the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "colour repeat",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "colour-repeat"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " aligning with the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "threading draft",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "threading-draft"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". For the M's and O's structure, the warp colour repeat must be 8 ends long: ends 1-4 are colour A, ends 5-8 are colour B, repeating. This colour grouping corresponds to the block threading below."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "M's and O's: the four-shaft colour-and-weave threading"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "M's and O's",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "ms-and-os"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " structure divides the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "warp",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "warp"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " into two blocks. Block A (shafts 1 and 3) and Block B (shafts 2 and 4) alternate in groups of four ends. The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "threading draft",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "threading-draft"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " for one 8-end repeat is: 1, 3, 1, 3, 2, 4, 2, 4 (Block A followed by Block B). The same two-pick treadling is used throughout: shaft 1+2 together, then shaft 3+4 together. The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "colour-and-weave",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "colour-and-weave"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " effect appears because the two blocks behave like independent log-cabin units."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "weavingDraft",
        "attrs": {
          "definition": {
            "title": "M's and O's colour-and-weave, 4 shafts",
            "loomType": "floor-loom",
            "threading": [
              1,
              3,
              1,
              3,
              2,
              4,
              2,
              4,
              1,
              3,
              1,
              3,
              2,
              4,
              2,
              4
            ],
            "tieUp": [
              [
                1,
                0,
                1,
                0
              ],
              [
                0,
                1,
                0,
                1
              ]
            ],
            "treadling": [
              1,
              2,
              1,
              2,
              1,
              2,
              1,
              2
            ]
          }
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Assign colour A to all ends on shafts 1 and 3; assign colour B to all ends on shafts 2 and 4. Thread the colour with the end: whenever you thread an end on shaft 1 or 3, use colour A yarn; whenever you thread shaft 2 or 4, use colour B yarn. The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "colour repeat",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "colour-repeat"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " then aligns automatically with the threading blocks."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Weaving the sample"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Step 1: Wind on the warp in strict colour-repeat order: 4 ends colour A, 4 ends colour B, repeating. Use separate spools for each colour and load both onto the warping board bracket at the same time, tying off and switching every 4 ends."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Step 2: Thread the "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "threading draft",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                        "attrs": {
                          "termSlug": "threading-draft"
                        }
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": 1, 3, 1, 3 (colour A), 2, 4, 2, 4 (colour B), repeating across the full width. Thread right to left."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Step 3: Set up the tie-up: treadle 1 lifts shafts 1 and 2; treadle 2 lifts shafts 3 and 4."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Step 4: Load one shuttle with colour A "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "weft",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                        "attrs": {
                          "termSlug": "weft"
                        }
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " and one with colour B. Weave the sample with alternating colour A / colour B weft on consecutive picks. This produces the full "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "colour-and-weave",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                        "attrs": {
                          "termSlug": "colour-and-weave"
                        }
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " effect."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Step 5: To see the block effect, try several picks of colour A only, then several picks of colour B only. Each produces a different stripe character in the two threading blocks."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "items": [
            {
              "problem": "The colour blocks are not showing; the cloth looks like plain stripes",
              "solution": "The warp colour repeat is not aligned with the threading. Check that colour A is exclusively on shafts 1 and 3, and colour B exclusively on shafts 2 and 4. If any colour-A end is on shaft 2 or 4, the block breaks down."
            },
            {
              "problem": "The sample looks blurred and the block boundaries are unclear",
              "solution": "The two weft colours may be too similar in value (lightness/darkness). Colour-and-weave effects rely on strong contrast. Try the same threading with a much higher-contrast colour pair to assess whether the structure is correct."
            },
            {
              "problem": "The tie-up is producing twill lines rather than the colour-and-weave blocks",
              "solution": "The treadle tie-up is incorrect. Shafts 1 and 2 must lift together on treadle 1; shafts 3 and 4 together on treadle 2. Do not use the advancing 1-2-3-4 twill tie-up."
            }
          ]
        }
      }
    ]
  }
}
